[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     70[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe HIPAA Privacy Rule's minimum-necessary requirement and the 21st Century Cures Act information-blocking rules both depend on the identity boundary. A read of the identity record that exposes a patient's prior name to a caller without a need-to-know is a minimum-necessary violation and (for sensitivity-classified prior names) a dignity failure that the patient experiences directly. A write or invalidation event that succeeds without proving the originating principal does not have the audit-trail attribution that compliance and patient-trust both require. A sensitivity-class-downgrade event that succeeds without dual control is a uniquely consequential failure mode that no prior recipe in the chapter has at this severity.[K
