[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    180[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe cohort-axis enumeration is recipe-specific and dignity-consequential.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The Honest Take names "patients with names from non-dominant-culture naming traditions" and "transgender patients" as cohorts that experience more matcher errors and more operational friction respectively; the TODO at line 341 names "name-tradition cohort, transgender-or-gender-diverse cohort with patient-consented self-identification only, name-change-frequency cohort, age-of-name-change cohort." The transgender-or-gender-diverse cohort is uniquely sensitive (the cohort label itself is sensitivity-classified data; the bucketed-cohort-label discipline from Finding S4 applies with extra force); the name-tradition cohort axis is recipe-specific and is the dominant driver of cohort disparity in name-change handling per the Honest Take's "the matcher's reference data is the dominant source of cohort-disparity" framing.[K
